    "recap_headline": "Abilene Christian",
    "recap_text": "ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. - Three Wildcats hit home runs as Abilene Christian baseball fell to New Mexico 11-5 at Lobo Baseball Field on Sunday afternoon. ACU, a top-20 program in the nation for long balls, went deep 10 times over the weekend as it picked up the series victory.\nThe Wildcats continue their eight-game road trip versus Stephen F. Austin in Nacogdoches, Texas at 6 p.m. Wednesday. ACU then heads to Lake Charles, La. to play McNeese on March 27-29 in its final series before conference play begins.\nRyan Jones\n,\nGrant Watkins\nand\nSam Hardcastle\neach went yard for the Wildcats, with Watkins picking up his 12th home run of the season. He is second in the Western Athletic Conference in long balls, trailing only teammate\nDiego Cardenas\nwith 13.\nJones paced ACU with two hits and two runs batted in. Six of the Wildcats' eight hits were for extra bases as Jones, Cardenas and\nJT Thompson\ndoubled. Cardenas and Thompson extended their hitting streaks to seven games, while\nZandt Payne\nreached base safely for the 18th game in a row.\nCarson Wallace\n,\nCollin Adams\nand\nGrayson McKelvey\ncombined for two scoreless innings out of the bullpen, with Adams making his first appearance of the season. Wallace struck out a pair.\nACU wasn't able to rally from an early deficit for the third game in a row as New Mexico grabbed an 8-0 lead through five innings. Thompson's leadoff double in the sixth gave way to Jones' second home run of the season, a two-run blast. Payne followed with a walk, and Cardenas brought him home with an RBI double.\nThe Wildcats added a couple more runs in the ninth with back-to-back solo homers by Watkins, a Los Alamos, N.M. native, and Hardcastle.",
